  "dialogue": "# Collaboration History\n\n**Task**: Read <workspace>/ENVIRONMENT.md first — it explains the test setup and how to run tests. Then read <workspace>/requirement.xml and implement the requirements. Work only in <workspace>/code/. Run tests with: docker exec -w /app/code -e PYTHONPATH=src:. <container>_rll python -m pytest tests --tb=short -q\n**Started**: 2026-03-24 22:14:01\n\n---\n\n## [Ralph] [PLAN] Round 1 | Step: planning\n**Time**: 2026-03-24 22:16:44\n**Summary**: \n\n[PLAN]\n\n## Task Goal\nAdd cursor-based pagination classes and new Skills/Versions beta resources to the Anthropic Python SDK so that 20 tests in `test_skills.py` and `test_versions.py` pass.\n\n## Understanding\nThe tests import types and resources that don't exist yet. I need to create:\n1. `SyncPageCursor` / `AsyncPageCursor` pagination classes\n2. Skill response types (`SkillCreateResponse`, etc.)\n3. Version response types (`VersionCreateResponse`, etc.)\n4. Skills resource with CRUD methods\n5. Versions sub-resource under Skills\n6. Wire everything into `beta.py` and `__init__.py` exports\n\n## Proposed Approach\n\n### Req 1: Cursor-based pagination (`pagination.py`)\nAdd `SyncPageCursor[_T]` and `AsyncPageCursor[_T]` to `pagination.py`, following the existing `SyncPage`/`AsyncPage` pattern but using `next_cursor`/`page` instead of `after_id`/`before_id`.\n\n### Req 2: Skill response types (`types/beta/`)\nCreate 4 minimal Pydantic models: `SkillCreateResponse`, `SkillRetrieveResponse`, `SkillListResponse`, `SkillDeleteResponse` — each extending `BaseModel`. Export from `types/beta/__init__.py`.\n\n### Req 3: Version response types (`types/beta/skills/`)\nCreate new `types/beta/skills/` package with 4 models: `VersionCreateResponse`, `VersionRetrieveResponse`, `VersionListResponse`, `VersionDeleteResponse`. Export from its `__init__.py`.\n\n### Req 4: Skills resource (`resources/beta/skills/`)\nCreate `skills.py` with `Skills`/`AsyncSkills` resource classes implementing:\n- `create()` → POST `/v1/beta/skills`\n- `retrieve(skill_id)` → GET `/v1/beta/skills/{skill_id}` (ValueError on empty)\n- `list()` → GET `/v1/beta/skills` returning `SyncPageCursor[SkillListResponse]`\n- `delete(skill_id)` → DELETE `/v1/beta/skills/{skill_id}` (ValueError on empty)\n\nPlus `SkillsWithRawResponse`, `AsyncSkillsWithRawResponse`, `SkillsWithStreamingResponse`, `AsyncSkillsWithStreamingResponse` wrappers.\n\nWire into `Beta`/`AsyncBeta` in `beta.py` as `skills` cached property.\n\n### Req 5: Versions sub-resource (`resources/beta/skills/versions.py`)\nCreate `Versions`/`AsyncVersions` resource classes implementing:\n- `create(skill_id)` → POST `/v1/beta/skills/{skill_id}/versions`\n- `retrieve(version, *, skill_id)` → GET `/v1/beta/skills/{skill_id}/versions/{version}`\n- `list(*, skill_id)` → GET `/v1/beta/skills/{skill_id}/versions`\n- `delete(version, *, skill_id)` → DELETE `/v1/beta/skills/{skill_id}/versions/{version}`\n\nAll with appropriate ValueError checks on empty path params.\n\nWire into `Skills`/`AsyncSkills` as `versions` cached property.\n\n## Expected Deliverables\n- Modified: `pagination.py`, `types/beta/__init__.py`, `resources/beta/beta.py`, `resources/beta/__init__.py`\n- New: 4 skill type files, `types/beta/skills/__init__.py` + 4 version type files, `resources/beta/skills/__init__.py` + `skills.py` + `versions.py`\n\n## Test Plan\n- **Test command**: `docker exec -w /app/code -e PYTHONPATH=src:. <container>_rll python -m pytest tests --tb=short -q`\n- **Expected**: All 20 non-passed tests become collectable and pass (8 in test_skills.py path_params, 12 in test_versions.py path_params)\n- **Scope**: path_params tests verify ValueError on empty string; skipped tests (prism binary) remain skipped\n\n## Quality Gate Commands\n- `docker exec -w /app/code -e PYTHONPATH=src:. <container>_rll python -c \"from anthropic.pagination import SyncPageCursor, AsyncPageCursor; print('OK')\"` — import check\n- `docker exec -w /app/code -e PYTHONPATH=src:. <container>_rll python -c \"from anthropic.types.beta import SkillListResponse, SkillCreateResponse, SkillDeleteResponse, SkillRetrieveResponse; print('OK')\"` — type import check\n\n\n---\n\n## [Lisa] [NEEDS_WORK] Round 1 | Step: planning\n**Time**: 2026-03-24 22:18:30\n**Summary**: The submission is still only a plan, not an implementation. `work.md:3` and `work.md:22` describe intended changes, but there is no `[CODE]`/`[FIX]` section and the source still lacks the foundational pagination classes: `code/src/anthropic/pagination.py:8` exports only `SyncPage`/`AsyncPage`, and `code/src/anthropic/pagination.py:13` plus `code/src/anthropic/pagination.py:50` define only those two classes. As a result, the required beta tests still fail during collection with `ImportError: cannot import name 'SyncPageCursor'`.\n\n[NEEDS_WORK] The submission is still only a plan, not an implementation. `work.md:3` and `work.md:22` describe intended changes, but there is no `[CODE]`/`[FIX]` section and the source still lacks the foundational pagination classes: `code/src/anthropic/pagination.py:8` exports only `SyncPage`/`AsyncPage`, and `code/src/anthropic/pagination.py:13` plus `code/src/anthropic/pagination.py:50` define only those two classes. As a result, the required beta tests still fail during collection with `ImportError: cannot import name 'SyncPageCursor'`.\n\nI reran the required test command exactly as specified: `docker exec -w /app/code -e PYTHONPATH=src:. <container>_rll python -m pytest tests --tb=short -q`. It exited `1` with `340 failed, 563 passed, 91 skipped, 98 errors in 41.86s`, including the collection errors from `tests/api_resources/beta/test_skills.py` and `tests/api_resources/beta/skills/test_versions.py`. Please implement the planned files and resubmit with actual test results from the implementation round.\n\n",
